# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Speed Insights for the professors-platform React application following the official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` package (v1.3.1) to the project dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json to reflect the new dependency and its transitive dependencies

### 2. Modified Files
- **src/App.tsx**: Added SpeedInsights component integration
  - Imported `SpeedInsights` from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component

### Implementation Details
The SpeedInsights component was added to the root App component, which ensures it tracks performance metrics across all routes in the application. This follows the recommended pattern for React applications using React Router.

The implementation is consistent with the existing code structure:
- Placed next to the existing Vercel Analytics component for logical grouping
- Uses the same import pattern as other Vercel packages
- Maintains the existing JSX structure and formatting

### Verification
- ✅ Build completed successfully without errors
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced
